Destroying angels are among the most toxic known mushrooms; both they and the closely related {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amanita_phalloides"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 death caps}} (
\f2\i A. phalloides
\f0\i0 ) contain {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amatoxin"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 amatoxins}}.{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Destroying_angel#cite_note-AmanitaGenus-1"}}{\fldrslt 
\fs20 \cf3 \super \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 [1]}} \
